- Sun 1 Sep 2019. Ebola funding
Actualite [Google transl, edited]
https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2019/09/drc-only-15-of-ebola-funding-available-ant%C3%B3nio-guterres-launches-alarm.htm

DRC: Only 15% of Ebola funding available; Antonio Guterres launches alarm

Antonio Guterres, Secretary-General of the United Nations, visited the territory of Beni on Sun 1 Sep 2019. In particular, he raised the issue of financing the 4th Ebola response plan.

"We need greater solidarity from the international community. The pledges up to the end of the year [2019] correspond more or less to the need for Ebola control, but only 15% have been paid so far. There is a problem of liquidity," he told the microphone of Actualite.CD.

Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3023, of which 2918 were confirmed and 105 probable. In total, there were 2024 deaths (1919 confirmed and 105 probable) and 902 people healed.

"When there is no cash, even if there are promises, the response against Ebola stops. If you lose a week in the Ebola response, you can lose the war on Ebola. Ebola does not wait. All the countries and organizations that have made financial commitments must be able to fulfill their promises so that the vigorous response I have seen here can continue uninterrupted," he added.

He suggested that partners accelerate the pace of disbursement.

"Payments are still very limited. We cannot stop the response while waiting for the money," hammered the UN No. 1 again.

The World Bank announced on 23 Aug 2019 that USD 50 million will be donated to the World Health Organization (WHO) to "fund its operational activities to save lives in the context of frontline responses to the epidemic."

This funding is part of the USD 300 million financial package announced by the World Bank last month [August 2019] to support the 4th Ebola Strategic Response Plan (SRP4). The USD 300 million covers more than half of the needs of the SRP4.

